gmd:MD_TopologyLevelCode/topology1D/desc:
1-dimensional topological complex -- commonly called chain-node
			topology
gmd:MD_TopologyLevelCode/planarGraph/des:
1-dimensional topological complex that is planar. (A planar graph is a graph
				that can be drawn in a plane in such a way that no two edges intersect except at a
				vertex.)
gmd:MD_TopologyLevelCode/fullPlanarGraph:
2-dimensional topological complex that is planar. (A 2-dimensional topological
				complex is commonly called full topology in a cartographic 2D
			environment.)
gmd:MD_TopologyLevelCode/surfaceGraph/de:
1-dimensional topological complex that is isomorphic to a subset of a surface.
				(A geometric complex is isomorphic to a topological complex if their elements are in a
				one-to-one, dimensional-and boundry-preserving correspondence to one
			another.)
gmd:MD_TopologyLevelCode/fullSurfaceGrap:
2-dimensional topological complex that is isomorphic to a subset of a
			surface
gmd:MD_TopologyLevelCode/topology3D/desc:
3-dimensional topological complex. (A topological complex is a collection of
				topological primitives that are closed under the boundary operations.)
gmd:MD_TopologyLevelCode/fullTopology3D/: Complete coverage of a 3D Euclidean coordinate space
gmd:MD_TopologyLevelCode/abstract/descri: Topological complex without any specified geometric realisation
